This paper is primarily focused on the design and analysis of a data structure for dynamic dictionaries, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves probabilistic analysis and queueing techniques, which are relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The experimental results presented in the paper involve simulations of the data structure, which could be considered numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the data structure in high-performance routing, which could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
